cation networks, other technologies such as nanotechnology, smart technologies, robotics, location, etc. will also enable different Internet of Things services.  Wireless-based Internet of Things services is more popular since the RFID and sensors will provide information through the radio interface. The wired commu- nication between objects will mainly be the power line communication since the home electronic appliances considered then as objects will take advantage of the electrical communication to also send information. When home networking appli- cation has started at the same time as PLC development, these applications were named home networking applications. With the introduction of wireless RFID and sensors, new applications can be developed in home networking but also every- where involving the real world objects, and then the world of Internet of Things is used to better cover all these existing and emerging new services and applica- tions interacting with the real world. RFID technology, sensor technology are the close to market enabling technologies of the IoT as they enable the object or the thing to be connected to the network and they are offering the possibility to develop new services based on wireless communication. On the other hand, PLC technology provides a natural connection to other type of objects, not tiny ones, they are home electronic appliances and show other applications of Internet of Thing in the home networking using wired link such as PLC and these are actually new applications compared to classical applications that we can get through computers or telephones using the classical technologies such as ﬁxed or mobile communication. These other communication technologies such as ethernet, wireless, and mobile communication technologies are connecting devices such as computers or telephones  ﬁxed or mo- biles  but we prefer to not consider these devices as objects or things, since they are   172  Passive RFID  Table 9.1 RFID tag technolog